House Bill 803
By: Representative Hatchett of the 155th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To provide a homestead exemption from City of Dublin independent school district ad
2 valorem taxes for educational purposes in the amount of $7,000.00 of the assessed value of
3 the homestead for residents of that school district who are between 62 and 64 years of age;
4 to provide a homestead exemption from City of Dublin independent school district ad
5 valorem taxes for educational purposes in the amount of $14,000.00 of the assessed value of
6 the homestead for residents of that school district who are between 65 and 72 years of age;
7 to provide a homestead exemption from City of Dublin independent school district ad
8 valorem taxes for educational purposes in the amount of $21,000.00 of the assessed value of
9 the homestead for residents of that school district who are between 73 and 79 years of age;
10 to provide a homestead exemption from City of Dublin independent school district ad
11 valorem taxes for educational purposes in the full amount of the assessed value of the
12 homestead for residents of that school district who are 80 years of age or older; to provide
13 that such exemption shall only apply to tax years 2026 through 2030; to provide for
14 definitions; to specify the terms and conditions of the exemption and the procedures relating
15 thereto; to provide for applicability; to provide for compliance with constitutional
16 requirements; to provide for a referendum, effective dates, automatic repeal, mandatory
17 execution of election, and judicial remedies regarding failure to comply; to provide for
18 related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
