19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
20 SECTION 1.
21 (a) As used in this Act, the term:
22 (1) "Ad valorem taxes for educational purposes" means all ad valorem taxes for
23 educational purposes levied by, for, or on behalf of the City of Dublin independent school
24 district, except for any ad valorem taxes to pay interest on and to retire independent
25 school district bonded indebtedness.
26 (2) "Homestead" means homestead as defined and qualified in Code Section 48-5-40 of
27 the O.C.G.A., as amended, with the additional qualification that it shall include not more
28 than five contiguous acres of homestead property.
29 (b)(1) Each resident of the City of Dublin independent school district who is between 62
30 and 64 years of age is granted an exemption on such person's homestead from City of
31 Dublin independent school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the
32 amount of $7,000.00 of the assessed value of such homestead. The value of that property
33 in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
34 (2) Each resident of the City of Dublin independent school district who is between 65
35 and 72 years of age is granted an exemption on such person's homestead from City of
36 Dublin independent school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the
37 amount of $14,000.00 of the assessed value of such homestead. The value of that
38 property in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
39 (3) Each resident of the City of Dublin independent school district who is between 73
40 and 79 years of age is granted an exemption on such person's homestead from City of
41 Dublin independent school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the
42 amount of $21,000.00 of the assessed value of such homestead. The value of that
43 property in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
